Articles.Content:
After some time away from working on KSP stuff (Thanks, Steam Winter Sale...), I'm back and made some progress on Mk3 stuff - have some WIP advanced engines:

![pn0jgYc.png](http://i.imgur.com/pn0jgYc.png)

@ZobrAA: Because it seemed to work somewhat better, the docking port itself has been removed, and the part is now a alternate form for the existing engine shroud, so it could be used in the way you describe.

Got the mk3 nuclear jet in game, functionality is the same as the mk2 version (functions in any atmosphere, optional nuclear decay patch)![0Pru8v2.png](http://i.imgur.com/0Pru8v2.png)

Next update will happen when KSP 1.1 does Expect the new engines, docking ports, symmetry fixes for the chines/saddle tanks, possibly one or two other things.

@TruthQuark: The mk3 nuclear rocket's stats at present are 13.5 tons, 400 KN thrust, for a TWR of 3.02.

@Kerbas\_ad\_astra: Sure, that would be a good thing to add. Consider it done.
